Several other methods are available for measuring ketone bodies 
With the isolation and purification of the enzyme  hydroxybutyrate dehydrogenase  it became possible to develop a sensitive and highly specific enzymatic assay for acetoacetate and hydroxybutyrate 
The enzyme catalyzes the redox reaction 
More recently  fluorometric techniques and an automated colorimetric method have been developed for this analysis  and other enzymatic methods have been described for the determination of acetoacetate 
Finally  Kobayashi and co workers  have developed a gas chromatographic method for the determination of both acetone and acetoacetate in urine 
They speculate that the method could be easily adapted to measure hydroxybutyrate as well  following its quantified oxidation to acetoacetate 
